				\begin{document}$${{\rm{OH}}}^{\bullet }$$\end{document}) through oxidation of OH− by photo induced holes rendering the composite film highly reactive during photocatalysis.

From the Hall effect analysis, the Hall coefficient is found to be negative for all the thin films which indicates that they are n- type semiconductors. Generally, TiO2 is an intrinsic n-type semiconductor8. The formation of the OVs and titanium interstitials are responsible for this sort of conductivity54. TiO2 is a sub-stoichiometric compound with excess titanium under standard conditions. This sub -stoichiometry is accommodated as OVs or titanium interstitials formation. The following reaction mechanisms can be considered for the formation of OVs in TiO2 crystal55:10OOx→TiO212O2(g)+VO••+2e'\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
